17 Section 308.3. A. The Legislature shall have joint resolutions
18 prepared for consideration each session.
19 B. For the purpose of this section, a proposed permanent rule
20 may be disapproved, in whole or in part, in a joint resolution
21 considered by the Legislature.
22 C. If any rule received on or before the date established
23 pursuant to paragraph 1 of subsection A of Section 308 of this title
24 is not subject to a joint resolution passed by both houses of the
